7 (11) (a) "Temporary total disability" means the condition of an employee who has not
8 reached maximum medical improvement from an injury and has not reached a
9 level of improvement that would permit a return to employment;
10 (b) "Permanent partial disability" means the condition of an employee who, due
11 to an injury, has a permanent disability rating but retains the ability to work;
12 and
13 (c) "Permanent total disability" means the condition of an employee who, due to
