19 shall be the projected value of the employer's workers' compensation claims for the
20 next calendar year as calculated by the commissioner using generally-accepted
21 actuarial methods as follows:
22 (a) The base period shall be the earliest three (3) calendar years of the five (5)
23 calendar years immediately preceding the calendar year for which the
24 calculation is made. The commissioner shall identify each claim of the
25 employer which has an injury date or date of last injurious exposure to the
26 cause of an occupational disease during each one (1) of the three (3) calendar
27 years to be used as the base, and shall assign a value to each claim. The value
Page 9 of 55
BR140200.100 - 1402 - XXXX 3/10/2026 2:38 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1402
1 shall be the total of the indemnity benefits paid to date and projected to be
2 paid, adjusted to current benefit levels, plus the medical benefits paid to date
3 and projected to be paid for the life of the claim, plus the cost of medical and
4 vocational rehabilitation paid to date and projected to be paid. Adjustment to
5 current benefit levels shall be done by multiplying the weekly indemnity
6 benefit for each claim by the number obtained by dividing the statewide
7 average weekly wage which will be in effect for the year for which the
8 premium is being calculated by the statewide average weekly wage in effect
9 during the year in which the injury or date of the last exposure occurred. The
10 total value of the claims using the adjusted weekly benefit shall then be
11 calculated by the commissioner. Values for claims in which awards have been
12 made or settlements reached because of findings of permanent partial or
13 permanent total disability shall be calculated using the mortality and interest
14 discount assumptions used in the latest available statistical plan of the
15 advisory rating organization defined in Subtitle 13 of KRS Chapter 304. The
16 sum of all calculated values shall be computed for all claims in the base
17 period;
18 (b) The commissioner shall obtain the annual payroll for each of the three (3)
19 years in the base period for each employer carrying his own risk from records
20 of the department and from the records of the Department of Workforce
21 Development, Education and Labor Cabinet. The commissioner shall multiply
22 each of the three (3) years of payroll by the number obtained by dividing the
23 statewide average weekly wage which will be in effect for the year in which
24 the premium is being calculated by the statewide average weekly wage in
25 effect in each of the years of the base period;
26 (c) The commissioner shall divide the total of the adjusted claim values for the
27 three (3) year base period by the total adjusted payroll for the same three (3)
