20 Section 3. KRS 342.120 is amended to read as follows:
21 (1) There is created the Division of Workers' Compensation Funds in the Department
22 of Workers' Claims that[which] shall be responsible for the administration of the
23 special fund and the coal workers' pneumoconiosis fund and the maintenance of
24 records regarding the payment of claims by these funds. The Division of Workers'
25 Compensation Funds shall have no responsibility for the coal workers'
26 pneumoconiosis fund once the assets and liabilities have been transferred to the
27 Kentucky Employers' Mutual Insurance Authority, which will administer the fund
Page 13 of 55
BR140200.100 - 1402 - XXXX 3/10/2026 2:38 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1402
1 pursuant to KRS 342.1243. The Division of Workers' Compensation Funds shall be
2 headed by a director appointed by the commissioner[secretary of the Education and
3 Labor Cabinet], with the prior written approval of the Governor pursuant to KRS
4 12.050. The director shall be responsible for overseeing the administration of the
5 funds and the maintenance of records regarding the payment of claims by the funds.
6 (2) The special fund shall have no liability upon any claim in which the injury
7 occurred, or for cumulative trauma, the disability became manifest, or, for
8 occupational disease, if the date of injury or last exposure occurred, after December
9 12, 1996.
10 (3) Where the employer has settled its liability for income benefits and thereafter a
11 determination has been made of the special fund's liability, the special fund portion
12 of the benefit rate shall be paid over the maximum period provided for by statute
13 for that disability, with the period of payment beginning on the date settlement was
14 approved by an administrative law judge. This provision is remedial and shall apply
15 to all pending and future claims.
