5 premium and the amount to be paid for assessments. No insurance carrier shall
6 collect from an insured an amount in excess of the assessment percentages imposed
7 by this chapter. The assessment for an insurance policy or other evidence of
8 coverage providing a deductible may be collected in accordance with this chapter
9 on a premium amount that equates to the premium that would have applied without
10 the deductible. The percentages imposed by this chapter for an insurance policy
11 issued by an insurance company shall be those percentages in effect on the annual
12 effective date of the policy, regardless of the date that the premium is actually
13 received by the insurance company.
14 (4) A self-insured group may elect to report its premiums and to have its assessments
15 computed in the same manner as insurance companies. This election may not be
16 rescinded for at least ten (10) years, nor may this election be made a second time
17 for at least another ten (10) years, except that the board of directors of the funding
18 commission may, at its discretion, waive the ten (10) year ban on a case-by-case
19 basis after formal petition has been made to the funding commission by a self-
20 insured group.
21 (5) The funding commission, as part of the collection and auditing of the special fund
22 assessments required by this section, shall annually require each insurance carrier
23 and each self-insured group to provide a list of employers which it has insured or
24 which are members and the amount collected from each employer. Additionally, the
25 funding commission shall require each entity paying a special fund assessment to
26 report the SIC code for each employer and the amount of premium collected from
27 each SIC code. An insurance carrier or self-insured group may require its insureds
