4 Section 7. KRS 342.230 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) The commissioner shall establish and fill any positions, including medical
6 services and advice, necessary to carry on the department's work subject to the
7 limits of appropriations for the department and except as otherwise required by
8 law. All employees of the department shall be classified employees under KRS
9 Chapter 18A, except for the commissioner, the administrative law judges, and
10 board members. The commissioner shall have immediate supervision of the
11 employees of the department, perform duties assigned to him or her, and have
12 complete authority to carry out all the administrative functions relating to the
13 department.
14 (2) The commissioner with the assistance of the board shall train and instruct the
15 administrative law judges on an ongoing basis; assign cases; and monitor the
16 caseloads of the administrative law judges and the Workers' Compensation Board to
17 ensure timely disposition of cases; keep and be the custodian of the records of the
18 board and the administrative law judges; annually report the activities of the board
19 and the administrative law judges to the Governor; and devote his or her full time to
20 the duties of his or her office. The commissioner shall be paid a salary not less than
21 the salary of a member of the board.
22 (3)[(2)] The Governor shall appoint, with the consent of the Senate in accordance with
23 KRS 11.160 for a term of four (4) years, not more than nineteen (19) administrative
24 law judges, each of whom shall be an attorney and shall have five (5) years'
25 experience in the Commonwealth in the practice of workers' compensation law or a
26 related field, and extensive knowledge of workers' compensation law, and shall be
27 paid the same salary as a Circuit Judge. Each newly appointed administrative law
