5 Section 17. Upon the effective date of this Act, all records, files, documents,
6 equipment, staff, supporting budgets, and any and all unexpended funds associated with
7 the activities of the Department of Workers' Claims when it was attached to the
8 Education and Labor Cabinet shall be transferred to the Department of Workers' Claims
9 administratively attached to the Office of the Governor. All administrative regulations,
10 decisions, and actions promulgated, made, or taken by the Department of Workers'
11 Claims prior to the effective date of this Act that have not been repealed or rescinded
12 shall continue in effect on or after the effective date of this Act, unless and until they are
13 amended, repealed, or rescinded by the department after the effective date of this Act.
14 Section 18. Whereas it is critical to the proper management and administration
15 of the reorganized Department of Workers' Claims that consolidation take place as soon
16 as possible, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage
17 and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
